What's harder to buy than high speed rail tickets during the Spring Festival travel rush is COVID-19 masks.

Liu Yi knows this very well. She took annual leave and returned to her hometown in Hebei Province from Shenzhen, where she usually works, on January 16. It was hard to get a high-speed train ticket during the Spring Festival travel season, but she went home anyway. According to Liu, high-speed train tickets are just that, and masks are harder to buy than high-speed train tickets, especially N95 masks.

N95 Mask refers to the NIOSH approved by the United States, non-oil particulate filter efficiency greater than or equal to 95% mask. KN95 mask refers to a mask that meets the mandatory standard of Chinese GB 2626. The protective effect is equivalent to N95. In addition to industrial masks, medical masks, surgical masks also have the same protective effect.

It is worth noting that the general medical care masks, cotton masks and so on the virus protection effect is very limited, and e-commerce platform has a protective effect of masks sold out. JD.com platform sold more than 126m masks, 310,000 bottles of disinfectant and 1m bottles of hand sanitizer between January 19 and 22, according to JD.com. On January 22 alone, sales of face masks rose 48 times from the daily average of the previous month. The platform occasionally puts the goods consumer to have to fight hand in hand fast.

It is the Spring Festival holiday, most third-party merchants only receive orders not to ship, for orders after January 22, merchants promise to ship the date of February 1. Only a few third-party Spring Festival shipping business, the mask price set extremely high. HONEYVILLE, 3m and other well-known manufacturers of N95 mask products, has been sold to 50 yuan, the normal level of N95 mask prices of about 10 yuan.

Several e-commerce platforms, including Taobao, jd.com, ele.me and Suning E-commerce, have issued statements saying they will not allow price increases for face masks and other health products on the platforms. First financial inquiries after e-commerce site found that the Spring Festival shipment of N95 masks in an average price of 30 yuan.

The city with the greatest demand for medical consumables is Wuhan, which also appeals to the Society for medical consumables. On the evening of January 22, Alibaba said it had coordinated with 92 mask manufacturers in the country, which have a total inventory of 46.122 million masks available. These manufacturers expect to continue to produce 1.57 million masks before the holiday, and fully resume production after the holiday, the estimated daily production capacity is 16.289 million.

January 23, Netease Yanxuan said that through emergency coordination of production capacity, an additional batch of new masks, including 30,000 pieces of 3D protective masks exclusively for Hubei, priority free to Hubei users, can be collected by mail; Another 150,000 individually wrapped disposable masks are available for purchase nationwide.

Face masks are also hard to buy, not just online but offline. On the afternoon of the 22nd, China first finance visited some pharmacies in Handan, Hebei. N95 masks were generally out of stock. Some pharmacies said N95 could be ordered in the evening and sold for 25 yuan each. Asked about the mask brand, the pharmacy staff said that the N95 is now to rob, the pharmacy does not know the brand of masks, also do not know how much goods, the specific situation to wait for the arrival of masks to see.

On the morning of the 23rd, the pharmacy put the KN95 mask at the cash register. The clerk said the price of the mask was 30 yuan a piece. "The mask is now one price a day. " First financial visited other pharmacies in the city and found that, n90 masks, which filter non-oily particulate matter more than or equal to 90% , have also sold for 30 yuan each.
